<s1>
<ptxt>
Check that timing chain is installed properly as follows.
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Check that intake VVT actuator and exhaust VVT actuator marks (1) are aligned with top face of cylinder head (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A141006.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "46.550mm" ver = "01" gw = "219" gh = "115"/>
</figure>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Check that crankshaft pulley mark (1) is aligned with “0” (2) of timing chain cover.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A141007.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "45.815mm" ver = "01" gw = "164" gh = "113"/>
</figure>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Turn crankshaft clockwise fully twice and check again that match marks are aligned.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Be sure to turn crankshaft 720°. If it is turned only 360°, the timing marks (1) on intake VVT actuator and exhaust VVT actuator will not meet top face of cylinder head (2) as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A141006.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "46.550mm" ver = "01" gw = "219" gh = "115"/>
</figure>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
After turning crankshaft 720&#176;, the painted links of the timing chain will not be aligned with the timing marks on the intake VVT actuator and exhaust VVT actuator, but this is normal.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
</s2>
</s1>
